title: 12-001f13.jpg
description: The North America Tapestry of Time and Terrain. This map is a portrait of the land surface of North America and the ages of its underlying rock formations. This digital tapestry outlines the geologic story of continental collision and break-up, mountain-building, river erosion and deposition, ice-cap glaciation, volcanism, and other events and processes that have shaped the region over the last 2.6 billion years. (Image and text courtesy of the U.S. Geological Survey.)
alternate_text: A map of North America with colors that represent the ages of the underlying rocks.
credit: Image and text courtesy of the U.S. Geological Survey.
other_platform_requirements: Any number of image viewers/editors can be used to display these .jpg image files, including most html browsers.
